description:
Nowhere to Land



Aired on 03/09/2012, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 24 May 1988, TACA Airlines Flight 110, a near-new Boeing 737-300, flies through a thunderstorm and suffers a dual engine failure. The captain, Carlos Dardano, manages to make a successful deadstick landing on a narrow grass levee in the NASA Michoud Reservation area east of New Orleans.
